May be an image of 1 person, wrist watch and text that says 'cigar aficionado CAZINEFORME AVAILABLE ON NEWSSTANDS JULY 27T SPORTS BETTING GOES MOBILE AMERICAN WHISKEY COCKTAILS CIGAR SALES ARE BOOMING MY FAVORITE CIGAR ARMAND ASSANTE, ERIC RIPERT AND MORE cAM NEWTON THE CIGAR- LOVING PATRIOTS QUART ERBACK'.

node.text:
@Cameron1Newton is a dual-threat quarterback and a passionate cigar lover. The New England Patriot has a lot to say as the cover of the July/August issue of Cigar Aficionado. Plus, we take a look at American whiskey cocktails, online sports betting, golf's newest talents and the recent cigar boom. Click the link in our bio for the full table of contents.⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠

node.text:
Tea time with one of our Top 25 Cigars of 2020, the @highclerecastlecigar Victorian Toro. It’s made in Nicaragua by @foundationcigars and A.J. Fernandez of @ajfcigars. Better than a finger sandwich or scone, wouldn’t you say?⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠

node.text:
#CigaroftheWeek Southern Draw Cedrus Lancero from @sdcigars: This thin, lancero-style cigar is rolled with a dark wrapper and uncut foot, yet it draws quite well. Its spicy notes of ground red pepper are bridged by snaps of leather and coffee that lead to a sweeter toffee character and caramel finish.⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
⁠
#cigar #cigars #cigaraficionado #cigaraficionadomagazine #thegoodlife #nicaragua #nicaraguancigars

node.text: The @padroncigars family has been busy working on a new cigar. It’s short (less than 5 inches long), it’s fat (60 ring gauge) and it’s round. More info on our homepage at cigaraficionado.com

node.text:
